The paper deals with compressive sensing for video acquisition and recovery, which involves image and signal processing, information theory, machine learning, and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which covers topics such as image and video processing, object recognition, and scene understanding. The paper also involves the estimation of model parameters and the design of measurement strategies, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. Moreover, the paper uses a linear dynamical system (LDS) to model the evolution of the scene, which is a common approach in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Statistical Inference).
